Details:
We are dealing in this business for several years. We deal with .Net, 2D Animation, 3D Animation, Academic Projects, Adobe Flex, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, C Sharp (C#), Flash Action Effects, Graphic Designing Course, IEEE Projects, Java Script, Java/J2EE, Live Projects, MATLAB, MS Office, MS Project, Multimedia/Animation, Networking, , PHP & MySQL, Real Time Projects, Sound Forge, Spring, SQL Server 2005, VB Script, Visual Effects (VFX) Diploma and Web Designing.The animation industry in India is large & growing. Animation, gaming & web design professionals work on full-length animation movies, create TV commercials, education CDs, games for Internet, mobile, PC or consoles (like PlayStation or Xbox), work in the advertising industry or as web designers in various companies. 
The Price Waterhouse Coopers report on the Indian Entertainment & Media Industry estimated the Indian animation industry at Rs. 11 billion in 2006. It is forecast to grow at a rate of 22% per year & reach Rs. 29 billion by 2011. The Indian gaming industry was estimated at Rs. 2 billion in 2006 & is forecast to reach Rs. 28.5 billion by 2011 - growing at 68% per year.
Even at these impressive growth forecasts, the Indian animation & gaming industry will account for less than 2% of the worldwide market in 2010, clearly indicating a significantly larger opportunity. Indian studios work on animation projects for both, the Indian market as well as for international markets.

Details: TransWeave Solutions Pvt. Ltd. is a global firm with offices in India, USA and Canada offering complete end-to-end training and certification in SAP IS (Industry Solution) Retail in concert with SAP India education. Microsoft Dynamics AX content specific to industries (i.e. Retail, Discrete Manufacturing, Distribution, Process Manufacturing and Services).Microsoft Dynamics AX enables companies to remain relevant to the needs of the business and industry in todays highly competitive environment. Microsoft Dynamics AX enables companies to integrate their e-commerce abilities with existing IT investments and enables them to deliver breakthrough innovations. Microsoft certified Dynamics AX consultants command a high premium in ERP marketplace.

Details: NIIT Ltd. is a leading Global Talent Development Corporation, building skilled manpower pool for global industry requirements. The company which was set up in 1981, to help the nascent IT industry overcome its human resource challenges, has today grown to be amongst worlds leading talent development companies offering learning solutions to Individuals, Enterprises and Institutions across 40 countries. NIIT Ltd. expertise in learning content development, training delivery and education process management make it the most preferred training partner, worldwide. NIIT Ltd. has been ranked 4th in Best companies to work for in India, 2013-14, by Great Place to Work Institute and Top 10 Best Employers in India- 2011 by Aon Hewitt. The company has also been voted the second most trusted education brand in India by Brand Equity- Nielsen Survey 2011. Contact us for further details.

Animation, gaming & web design professionals work on full-length animation movies, create TV commercials, education CDs, games for Internet, mobile, PC or consoles (like PlayStation or Xbox), work in the advertising industry or as web designers in various companies. 
The Price Waterhouse Coopers report on the Indian Entertainment & Media Industry estimated the Indian animation industry at Rs. 11 billion in 2006. It is forecast to grow at a rate of 22% per year & reach Rs. 29 billion by 2011. The Indian gaming industry was estimated at Rs. 2 billion in 2006 & is forecast to reach Rs. 28.5 billion by 2011 - growing at 68% per year.
Even at these impressive growth forecasts, the Indian animation & gaming industry will account for less than 2% of the worldwide market in 2010, clearly indicating a significantly larger opportunity. Indian studios work on animation projects for both, the Indian market as well as for international markets.

Details:
Synergy focuses on training individuals on project management concepts and software tools such as Microsoft Office Project, MSP Server, Primavera, and Primavera Complete, Asta Power Project. The courses will be offered in 70 locations across India and in 7 countries, as listed in its website. 
Synergy also trains on PMP Certification Preparatory module, and conducts PME (Project Management Expert) Certification for PM Aspirants. 
The training outcome with Project Management Skills include: Realistic Budgeting, Resource Estimation, Testing Methods, Better Communication, and Effective Risk Management that keep the pace of production high, both qualitatively and quantitatively. Synergy enrolls Students and Professionals of Management and Engineering specialization viz., Mechanical, Civil, Electrical, Electronics, Instrumentation, Business Administration & IT
Synergy offers training on Tally software, MS Office and Placement Training through its course called Master Diploma in Business Automation. 
The School will also help students find employment in the relevant corporate firms for the respective programs.

Details: NIIT Ltd. is a leading Global Talent Development Corporation, building skilled manpower pool for global industry requirements. The company which was set up in 1981, to help the nascent IT industry overcome its human resource challenges, has today grown to be amongst worlds leading talent development companies offering learning solutions to Individuals, Enterprises and Institutions across 40 countries. Leading IT journal Dataquest has conferred upon NIIT the Top IT Training Company award successively for the past 20 years, since the inception of this category. NIIT Ltd. training solutions in IT, Banking, Finance and Insurance, Knowledge Process Outsourcing (KPO), Business Process Management (BPM), Executive Management Education, Vocational Skills, School Learning Solutions and Communication and Professional Life Skills has impacted over 35 million learners since inception. NIIT Ltd. expertise in learning content development, training delivery and education process management make it the most preferred training partner, worldwide. NIIT Ltd. has been ranked 4th in Best companies to work for in India, 2013-14, by Great Place to Work Institute and Top 10 Best Employers in India- 2011 by Aon Hewitt. The company has also been voted the second most trusted education brand in India by Brand Equity- Nielsen Survey 2011. Contact us for further details.

VIZKON TECHNOLOGIES began its journey a decade ago in marketing and service of electronics & computerized punching card systems for attendance and access control systems. The company has its good customer base in and around Coimbatore and all over Tamil Nadu and Kerala.
We step in here to cater the needs and requirements of the latest development in the industries such as Industrial Automation (Embedded-Designing, PLC, RTOS BSP  Device Driver  Networking), HR Solutions, Biometric & Smart-card based, Time & Attendance, Access Control Systems, Smart card, RFID-Inventory Systems, Payroll Packages, School, College & Hospital Management Software, E-Commerce, E-Marketing, Advertising & Promotional Events, E-Marketing research, Web Solutions, SEO (Search Engine Optimization), Branding and Total Design Solutions

To keep the momentum going, we have made a foray into the booming technology of embedded electronics and developments. Since then we are successfully and consistently designing and developing projects for engineering wards and customized design for industrial needs.VIZKON TECHNOLOGIES is an IT & Embeded design solutions provider. VIZKON Technologies was established in 2005 with a goal to provide dynamic and innovative solutions for industrial needs and we did as. Landscape of industrial control and monitoring has evolved we have remained at the forefront of technology.Our Vision & MissionVision 
Our ambivalent vision is to meet the technology demands as per Industrial need and implement it. We also provide the same to the students so as to enrich their potential with latest development and technologies in embedded systems and IT Solutions as per industrial standards. Mission
Our mission is to fill hardware and software on Real time implementation in embedded systems and IT technologies to excel them in this career.

Animation, gaming & web design professionals work on full-length animation movies, create TV commercials, education CDs, games for Internet, mobile, PC or consoles (like PlayStation or Xbox), work in the advertising industry or as web designers in various companies. 
The Price Waterhouse Coopers report on the Indian Entertainment & Media Industry estimated the Indian animation industry at Rs. 11 billion in 2006. It is forecast to grow at a rate of 22% per year & reach Rs. 29 billion by 2011. The Indian gaming industry was estimated at Rs. 2 billion in 2006 & is forecast to reach Rs. 28.5 billion by 2011 - growing at 68% per year.
Even at these impressive growth forecasts, the Indian animation & gaming industry will account for less than 2% of the worldwide market in 2010, clearly indicating a significantly larger opportunity. Indian studios work on animation projects for both, the Indian market as well as for international markets.

We are dealing in this business for several years. We deal with .Net, 2D Animation, 3D Animation, Academic Projects, Adobe Flex, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, C Sharp (C#), Flash Action Effects, Graphic Designing Course, IEEE Projects, Java Script, Java/J2EE, Live Projects, MATLAB, MS Office, MS Project, Multimedia/Animation, Networking, , PHP & MySQL, Real Time Projects, Sound Forge, Spring, SQL Server 2005, VB Script, Visual Effects (VFX) Diploma and Web Designing.The animation industry in India is large & growing. Animation, gaming & web design professionals work on full-length animation movies, create TV commercials, education CDs, games for Internet, mobile, PC or consoles (like PlayStation or Xbox), work in the advertising industry or as web designers in various companies. 
The Price Waterhouse Coopers report on the Indian Entertainment & Media Industry estimated the Indian animation industry at Rs. 11 billion in 2006. It is forecast to grow at a rate of 22% per year & reach Rs. 29 billion by 2011. The Indian gaming industry was estimated at Rs. 2 billion in 2006 & is forecast to reach Rs. 28.5 billion by 2011 - growing at 68% per year.
Even at these impressive growth forecasts, the Indian animation & gaming industry will account for less than 2% of the worldwide market in 2010, clearly indicating a significantly larger opportunity. Indian studios work on animation projects for both, the Indian market as well as for international markets.

Frameboxx Animation & Visual Effects is a versatile conglomerate with a focus on providing high end media and entertainment training & related services. Details: NIIT Ltd. is a leading Global Talent Development Corporation, building skilled manpower pool for global industry requirements. The company which was set up in 1981, to help the nascent IT industry overcome its human resource challenges, has today grown to be amongst worlds leading talent development companies offering learning solutions to Individuals, Enterprises and Institutions across 40 countries. Leading IT journal Dataquest has conferred upon NIIT the Top IT Training Company award successively for the past 20 years, since the inception of this category. NIIT Ltd. training solutions in IT, Banking, Finance and Insurance, Knowledge Process Outsourcing (KPO), Business Process Management (BPM), Executive Management Education, Vocational Skills, School Learning Solutions and Communication and Professional Life Skills has impacted over 35 million learners since inception. NIIT Ltd. expertise in learning content development, training delivery and education process management make it the most preferred training partner, worldwide. NIIT Ltd. has been ranked 4th in Best companies to work for in India, 2013-14, by Great Place to Work Institute and Top 10 Best Employers in India- 2011 by Aon Hewitt. The company has also been voted the second most trusted education brand in India by Brand Equity- Nielsen Survey 2011. Contact us for further details.

Details:
Maya Academy of Advanced Cinematics is a high-end 3D Animation & VFX education brand and situated in Heart of the City. The Institute has vast experience of teaching 3D & 2D Animation, VFX, Film making, Gaming, Web & Graphics Designing and Gaming. MAAC has a dedicated Research & Development team consisting of industry professionals. This team is responsible for planning the detailed curriculum for each course. The Academy conducts faculty training programs to ensure high standards of teaching in the classroom. All MAAC teachers are trained by Animation industry professionals who help sharpen their creative & technical skills.
MAAC lays strong emphasis on using the best infrastructure to train students. The Academy uses high-end computers, Wacom tablets & other equipment in the classroom. As a result, MAAC students often win many Awards for the films they create.

The year 2005 records batch strength of 40 scholars in the academy with a minimum of 5 batches per day. In the current year, the institute records student strength of 7000 members.
With a capacity for 100 students to get trained, video conferencing, overhead projectors and over 30 systems to accompany, the learning environment is really a benefaction to the pupils of the institute. The history rightly delivers that Systech Academy has reached great heights primarily through client satisfaction and commitment of the academy tutors.
Vision
To become a World known training academy that imparts quality training to young aspirants with skilled faculty, characteristic training modules and well equipped classrooms grounded on the evolving industry demands.
Mission
Our prime mission is to provide a practical approach and the best of strategies to our students to enable them attain total contentment."Satisfaction lies in the effort, not in the attainment, full effort is full victory." The effort that the students make in the 100% practical training leads them to victory. The students delight is the key ingredient of our success.

We are dealing in this business for several years. We deal with .Net, 2D Animation, 3D Animation, Academic Projects, Adobe Flex, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, C Sharp (C#), Flash Action Effects, Graphic Designing Course, IEEE Projects, Java Script, Java/J2EE, Live Projects, MATLAB, MS Office, MS Project, Multimedia/Animation, Networking, , PHP & MySQL, Real Time Projects, Sound Forge, Spring, SQL Server 2005, VB Script, Visual Effects (VFX) Diploma and Web Designing.The animation industry in India is large & growing. Animation, gaming & web design professionals work on full-length animation movies, create TV commercials, education CDs, games for Internet, mobile, PC or consoles (like PlayStation or Xbox), work in the advertising industry or as web designers in various companies. 
The Price Waterhouse Coopers report on the Indian Entertainment & Media Industry estimated the Indian animation industry at Rs. 11 billion in 2006. It is forecast to grow at a rate of 22% per year & reach Rs. 29 billion by 2011. The Indian gaming industry was estimated at Rs. 2 billion in 2006 & is forecast to reach Rs. 28.5 billion by 2011 - growing at 68% per year.
Even at these impressive growth forecasts, the Indian animation & gaming industry will account for less than 2% of the worldwide market in 2010, clearly indicating a significantly larger opportunity. Indian studios work on animation projects for both, the Indian market as well as for international markets.

Details:
We are dealing in this business for several years. We deal with .Net, 2D Animation, 3D Animation, Academic Projects, Adobe Flex, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop, C Sharp (C#), Flash Action Effects, Graphic Designing Course, IEEE Projects, Java Script, Java/J2EE, Live Projects, MATLAB, MS Office, MS Project, Multimedia/Animation, Networking, , PHP & MySQL, Real Time Projects, Sound Forge, Spring, SQL Server 2005, VB Script, Visual Effects (VFX) Diploma and Web Designing.The animation industry in India is large & growing. Animation, gaming & web design professionals work on full-length animation movies, create TV commercials, education CDs, games for Internet, mobile, PC or consoles (like PlayStation or Xbox), work in the advertising industry or as web designers in various companies. 
The Price Waterhouse Coopers report on the Indian Entertainment & Media Industry estimated the Indian animation industry at Rs. 11 billion in 2006. It is forecast to grow at a rate of 22% per year & reach Rs. 29 billion by 2011. The Indian gaming industry was estimated at Rs. 2 billion in 2006 & is forecast to reach Rs. 28.5 billion by 2011 - growing at 68% per year.
Even at these impressive growth forecasts, the Indian animation & gaming industry will account for less than 2% of the worldwide market in 2010, clearly indicating a significantly larger opportunity. Indian studios work on animation projects for both, the Indian market as well as for international markets.
